about.summary: pandas-highcharts is a Python package which allows you to easily build Highcharts plots with pandas.DataFrame objects.

name: pandas-highcharts
raw_recipe:
{% set version = "0.5.2" %}
{% set name = "pandas-highcharts" %}

package:
  name: {{ name }}
  version: {{ version }}

source:
  fn: {{ name }}-{{ version }}.tar.gz
  url: https://pypi.io/packages/source/{{ name[0] }}/{{ name }}/{{ name }}-{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: 2eace87c840dc430f40f739016f864df47721707feeeeb7db679218af73bcb22

build:
  number: 0
  script: python setup.py install --single-version-externally-managed --record=record.txt

requirements:
  build:
    - python
    - setuptools

  run:
    - python
    - pandas
    - ipython

test:
  imports:
    - {{ name.replace("-", "_") }}

about:
  home: https://github.com/gtnx/pandas-highcharts
  license_file: LICENSE
  license: MIT
  summary: 'pandas-highcharts is a Python package which allows you to easily build Highcharts plots with pandas.DataFrame objects.'

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - ericdill
    - mariusvniekerk
